(B) Raster plots of simulated LGN responses to 24 repeats of the 500-ms segment of a natural scene movie shown in (A). Burst events in the responses are highlighted. The colored arrows next to each burst event correspond to the luminance sequences in (A). Responses were simulated using an IFB model. The resting potential of the model (
							VR
							) and BP of the simulated response to a two-minute segment of natural scene movie that includes the 500-ms segment shown are indicated. The de-inactivation potential and threshold of the burst mechanism (
							VT
							) was −60 mV. For values of other model parameters, see 
							Materials and Methods.
